[quote=“Team_Rocket, post:7, topic:426679”][quote author=Uncalled link=topic=529374.msg3862792#msg3862792 date=1324765336]
As it isn’t a name and you’re defining it as a class, it would be grammatically incorrect to capitalize it. Pretty bad “Grammar Nazi” if you ask me. Also, to be grammatically correct, you would capitalize ‘grammar’ in ‘Grammar Nazi,’ as it’s a name, therefore would be a proper noun. You also capitalized “it’s” where it wasn’t needed and you added a comma before ‘and’ when it’s not needed. It’s not incorrect to add the comma, it’s just not needed.
[/quote]

Why are you starting up with me again? I don’t think this is the appropriate place. I graduated Highschool with an A in English, how about you?[/quote]A, if you speak English and fail to receive an A in your English class, you should give up… On everything.
